          <text>
                    <body>
                              <p rend="align(right)">
                                        <date>May 4<hi rend="sup">th</hi>. 49</date>
                              </p>
                              <p rend="indent(1)">Dear Friend,</p>
                              <p rend="indent(3)"><sic>Agreably</sic> to your request<lb/> I send
                                        you at once some more of Peritrol.<lb/> Little as it is, it
                                        is all I have ready<lb/> and is sufficient to rescue you
                                        from<lb/> the dilemma of sticking in the middle<lb/> of a
                                        paragraph. I will send you the<lb/> end of the chapter as
                                        soon as I possibly<lb/> can but I have been so very
                                        busy<lb/> as not to be able to pay any attention<lb/> to my
                                        article. I can do no more now<lb/> than to request you not
                                        to print further<lb/> than the words “his mission” on page
                                        25<lb/> as the next commences a new paragraph<lb/> and I
                                        have a note to use on page 26,<lb/> marked to This I will
                                        send you anon<lb/> Till then I am very sincerely yours</p>
                              <p rend="indent(3)">
                                        <persName role="author">Abraham de Sola</persName>
                              </p>
                              <p>Thanks for <persName>Gutheim's</persName> Sermon</p>
                    </body>
